    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-greek-cheese-tomato-and-chicken-farfalle/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then boil a kettle and take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with<strong> </strong>a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> chicken </strong>to the dish and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-greek-cheese-tomato-and-chicken-farfalle/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Crush your <strong>garlic </strong>open by squashing with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p><p>Add your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to the dish with your <strong>balsamic sundried tomato paste</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>dried basil</strong>, <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-greek-cheese-tomato-and-chicken-farfalle/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> pasta </strong>to the pot with your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and 500ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [650ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [850ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Tip: Nestle the pasta into the stock as much as you can for even cooking!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-greek-cheese-tomato-and-chicken-farfalle/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the pasta with your <strong>Greek cheese</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat </p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-greek-cheese-tomato-and-chicken-farfalle/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-greek-cheese-tomato-and-chicken-farfalle/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After an initial 15 min, remove the dish from the oven and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Return the dish to the oven, covered, and cook for a final 15-20 min or until the pasta is tender and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your<strong> oven baked Greek cheese, tomato & chicken farfalle</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-greek-cheese-tomato-and-chicken-farfalle/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>oven baked Greek cheese, tomato & chicken farfalle</strong> seasoned with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
